<br>
2) I guess the 'maintenence' on the Dreadlands zone last night was simply the add of static spawns in the ruins. What kind of maintenence is that?<br>
<br>
3) The corpse decay timer, why didn't they do this a long time ago?<br>
<br>
4) The new RandomSpawn (tm) timer on big MoB's after server reset. Does making the predictable, unpredictable and making the long wait, longer really make the game better? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrindal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krindal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/15/02 11:42:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10746.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think about some of these changes?</span><hr size=1> dont know much about the changes myself im only lvl 35 monk and dont know what alot of them do.  I talked to a friend of mine who is in an uber guild and he said that the random times on bug mob's is good for them but really bad for the &quot;non-uber&quot; guilds because the big ones are the only guilds that can throw together a raid on the spot. <p>Krindal<BR>35 Monk<BR>Mercenaries of Dark<BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92770">See My Stuff</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufalundirxviento.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falundir X Viento</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 947<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/16/02 12:31:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10746.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think about some of these changes?</span><hr size=1> Well to spawn a nice debate thats going around.  With the new changes to the end game, all they have succeded in doing is making things pointlessly harder or more annoying.<br>
<br>
Not going to list how things are more annoying, but the main problem I have is... Guilds that have not already had the time to reap the benifits of the end game, are now really pushed back from reaching it.  They have buffed things so that to guilds that are already in the end game, its just annoying to them.  For guilds that are just approaching it or are new to it, it's extreamly difficult due to lack of gear nessicary.  End game encounters are becoming more brute force and less stragety, which in my eyes really kills the appeal of the end game. <p><p><TABLE width="450">
