<br>
Walrus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator</font><br><font color=#A0B0E0>&#60;Silent Redemption&#62;</font></span><br>  Posts: 2709<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/16/02 2:46:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10746.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think about some of these changes?</span><hr size=1> 1) Eye of Zomm. <br>
<br>
It wasn't nerfed for that reason, it made pulling mobs easier, too easy in some cases.<br>
<br>
3) The corpse decay timer, why didn't they do this a long time ago?<br>
<br>
No clue, but it sure is a very nice feature.  I sure wish we had it... oh a month ago.  At least now I don't have to keep a timer running on uber mob corpses while we council loot.<br>
<br>
4) The new RandomSpawn (tm) timer on big MoB's after server reset. Does making the predictable, unpredictable and making the long wait, longer really make the game better? <br>
<br>
True Walrus, but also wasn't needed on Brell because there just aren't as many extremely powerful guilds like on other servers.  On Mith Marr for example there are 5 guilds that can completely destroy NToV, so there is both good and bad from the randomness for them.  On Brell that isn't the case, most of the high end mobs are only being killed by two alliances with a few others just being killed by one atm.  There is enough content that there are enough ubers to hit during the week on Brell.  On Mith Marr that isn't the case as it was all dying every patch day and then every week later as it respawned.<br>
<br>
The Statue/AoW change was very nice.  Guilds like Elysian, Drac, GotR have all been very cooperative trying to work out killing statue at a time that we could still get a shot at AoW.  At least now we don't have to worry about that,  they can kill Statue whenever they want and we can still get a shot at AoW when we have time.  (We as in SR/W and Ensh/LoH since they are attempting AOW now too)  previously it just made it impossible at times to get a shot at AoW, which is why Afterlife hadn't killed him in months, cause they never got to see statue up. <p><table><td><img src="http://members.aol.com/twiggiebrell/jaradissig.jpg"></td><td><TABLE STYLE="filter:GLOW(color=blue,strength=#+1)"  ><font color=white>Jaradis Stormcaller - 59th Luminary - Enemy to all of Velious<br>
Twiggie Tymberwolf - 52nd Wanderer - Friend to Dragon and Dwarves<br>Silent Redemption Member - Brell Serilis Server</font></table><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21764">Stats and Gear</a></td></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhawkline.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hawkline</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>D-O-R-K</span><br>  Posts: 2526<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/16/02 5:56:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10746.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think about some of these changes?</span><hr size=1> Someone posted on the PoN board that the corpse rez timer is bugged from the changes in decay time, and expiring after 3 hours online or offline (at least I think this is new), so don't camp until rezzed until futher notice. <p><p><font face="Arial">Hawkline<br>
Level 55 Knight of Mithaniel Marr<br>
Deus ex Machina</font></p><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jacmac>jacmac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/18/02 4:02:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10746.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think about some of these changes?</span><hr size=1> I saw a corpse timer say that a player had 144 hours 30 minutes left to rez, and 6 days... before decay. Sounds like something is wacked out with the timers... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeyangrey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keyan Grey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/18/02 10:55:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10746.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think about some of these changes?</span><hr size=1> I'm actually liking most of them.<br>
<br>
eye of zomm doesnt affect me, SKs have always had their own way to do this and it's still available to us. It did make some pulls way too easy though (to the point that any newb was able to split some spots).<br>
<br>
Res timer and poof timer are a good thing.<br>
<br>
Buffing mobs, as much as it hurts smaller guild not yet reaching the real end game was necessary. If you dont upgrade your mobs to remain a challenge they are just routine farming (FGs anyone ? come on i can SOLO them all!)<br>
<br>
I'm more torn about some changes like the perma rooting of some mobs... it makes pulling a lot easier in many places, and limits the safe spot camping problem... but doesnt seem to have any real impact other than being a pain in the ass.<br>
<br>
<br>
All in all, i think VI is starting to get their @#%$ together (yeah finally) and is actually designing encounters better lately, the random spawn timer is in my opinion a first step to making them less predictable.<br>
I dont think it'll have much of an impact on EQ, but hopefully it will teach something to the people designing online RPGs in the future. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=10746.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=10746.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10746.topic&index=7><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~eqmaximus/brell/addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.threadControl?topicID=10746.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10746.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10746.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm70">News and Events<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm58">The Outer Realm (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">The Hall of Honor<option value="brell